```

#### 3. Add workflow SSE route in `routes/mod.rs`

Add a dedicated route for RuntimeEvent-typed SSE alongside the existing
DashboardEvent SSE:

```rust
use crate::adapters::SseAdapter;
```

Add to `build_router` after the existing `.merge(sse::routes())`:

```rust
.route("/workflow/events", get(workflow_sse_handler))
```

The handler reads from an `SseAdapter` stored on `AppState`. If `AppState`
does not yet have an `sse_adapter` field, add it to `state.rs`:

```rust
pub sse_adapter: Arc<SseAdapter>,
```

Initialize in the `AppState` constructor with `Arc::new(SseAdapter::new(256))`.

The handler:

```rust
async fn workflow_sse_handler(
    State(state): State<Arc<AppState>>,
) -> Sse<impl Stream<Item = Result<Event, Infallible>>> {
    let rx = state.sse_adapter.subscribe();
    let stream = stream::unfold(rx, |mut rx| async move {
        loop {
            match rx.recv().await {
                Ok(sse_event) => {
                    let data = serde_json::to_string(&sse_event).unwrap_or_default();
                    let event = Event::default().event(sse_event.kind.clone()).data(data);
                    return Some((Ok(event), rx));
                }
                Err(broadcast::error::RecvError::Lagged(n)) => {
                    tracing::warn!(n, "workflow SSE client lagged");
                    continue;
                }
                Err(broadcast::error::RecvError::Closed) => return None,
            }
        }
    });
    Sse::new(stream).keep_alive(KeepAlive::default())
}
```

Import the necessary types at the top of `routes/mod.rs`. If `state.rs`
must be modified, limit changes to adding the `sse_adapter` field only.

